---
title: German Chicken with Creamy Dijon Sauce  plus Rosemary Potatoes & Roasted Carrots
description: Get ready for a hearty dinner inspired by our friends at HelloFresh Germany! You’ll elevate seared pork filets with a velvety Dijon cream sauce that cascades luxuriously over every bite. Serve with golden brown roasted rosemary potatoes and carrots, and sprinkle with herbaceous parsley for a meal that’s fit for weeknights and special occasions too.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66eaf8e28e45e3ca00862a7e-42f9cf07.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6762fd5c69731fa340b5b075-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/german-chicken-with-creamy-dijon-sauce-6762fd5c69731fa340b5b075
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
cuisine: Western Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 580 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 820 mg
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Finely chop @rosemary{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Toss potatoes on empty side of baking sheet with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{large drizzle}, chopped rosemary, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a second #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

> For beef or chicken, skip roasting in the oven and cook on stovetop until done.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Once veggies and chicken are done roasting, combine @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @water{2%tbsp}, and @pepper{pinch} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.

Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly with a #whisk{}, until slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> If sauce is too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches desired consistency.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and carrots between #plates{} in separate sections. Spoon sauce over chicken and potatoes and sprinkle with parsley. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.